{
  "answer": "**Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 43**, enumerates the requested sequence of twenty-one hells (*narakas*), among others, precisely matching the names and order given (with additional hells interspersed, such as Mahānaraka after Kālasūtra).[^1]\n\nThe named hells from the query appear in this order:\n\n> Tāmisra (Darkness). // Vi_43.2 //  \n> Andhatāmisra (Blinding Darkness). // Vi_43.3 //  \n> Raurava (Howling). // Vi_43.4 //  \n> Mahāraurava (Great Howling). // Vi_43.5 //  \n> Kālasūtra (The Black Thread). // Vi_43.6 //  \n> ...  \n> Saṃjīvana (Reviving). // Vi_43.8 //  \n> Avīci (Waveless). // Vi_43.9 //  \n> ...  \n> Kuḍmala (Bud). // Vi_43.14 //  \n> Pūtimṛttika (Putrid Clay). // Vi_43.15 //  \n> Lohaśaṅku (Iron Spike). // Vi_43.16 //  \n> ...  \n> Kaṇṭakaśālmali (Thorny Silk-Cotton Tree). // Vi_43.19 //  \n> ...  \n> Asipatravana (Forest of Sword-leaves). // Vi_43.21 //  \n> Lohacāraka (Iron Cage). // Vi_43.22 //\n\nIt then specifies the durations as requested:\n\n> In these, those who have committed heinous sins without performing *prāyaścitta* are tormented in succession for a Kalpa. // Vi_43.23 //[^2]  \n> Great sinners, for a Manvantara. // Vi_43.24 //\n\n[^1]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, *Chapter 43*, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/43/translation/#p-c760bd).\n\n[^2]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, *Chapter 43*, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/43/translation/#p-fc7b11).",
